name: landcover-gap2ha-1993-raster
notes: Data available online through GeoStor at http://www.geostor.arkansas.gov. This layer depicts 38 UNESCO/TNC based landcover categories for the State of Arkansas, which were derived from a digital classification of Landsat Thematic Mapper (TM) imagery, mostly from 1992, aggregated to a minimum mapping unit of 2 hectares. Categories: 1, T.1.A.9.b.I, Pinus echinata, shortleaf pine 2, T.1.A.9.b.II, Pinus taeda, loblolly pine 3, T.1.A.9.c.I, Juniperus virginiana, eastern red cedar 4, T.1.B.2.b.II, Quercus spp. - Pinus echinata -
